(In reply to comment #0) > The funny thing is that I'm running 4.2.2 but it uses @restoreEditors_e_3_8_2@
The javadoc for the method checking this says "Returns true if the environment supports the Eclipse 3.8.2/4.2.2 API for editor save and restore.", so I guess this is expected. I mean calling the @restoreEditors_e_3_8_2@ not the exception :)
If I got it right this is the failing assertion: @Assert.isTrue(inputs.length > 0);@ which looks to be caused by passing null @inputs@ and @mementos@ of size 0.
Thanks! Let's consider that fix for 3.9.1.
Sam, can you review and merge the fix?
Did you cherry-pick it onto the e_4_3_m_3_9_x branch? If yes we can close this bug (after adding the contributed keyword).
Sorry, but I don't get the commit when I pull. Did you push it already?
Lily confirms that she sees the commit on the branch too.
Awesome. I have too now. It was my mistake. Thanks!
